mission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell‚ÄôIdentit√† Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell‚ÄôIdentit√† Siciliana\" src=\"ISic030016-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text after Arena 1989 (IGASM I)\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Miller: ŒëœÄŒ≠..[[ŒΩ]]ŒΩ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511\">Valentina Mignosa\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[...] Myskon, son of Damis son of Kobetos [...] Anthemokritos bade Apellis offer security [...] said [...] was; he came upon [...] of the Leontines [...] Myskon sitting along the avenue [...] came (not?) having the money, the price of the cattle; he did not buy [...] went to Empedokles, son of Mnasimachos [...] let [...] become (liable?) to act as surety (trans. by Miller).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511\">Valentina Mignosa\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[...] Myskon, figlio di Damis figlio di Kobetos [...] Anthemokritos ordin√≤ ad Apelis(?) di agire da garante [...] disse [...] era; si imbatt√© [...] dei Leontini [...] Myskon seduto lungo il viale [...] venne (non?) avendo il denaro, il prezzo del bestiame; non compr√≤ [...] and√≤ da Empedokles, figlio di Mnasimachos [...] lasci√≤ che [...] diventasse garante.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Miller 1973 fig. p. 37 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002516\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscript